pageContext.claim: “They couldn't even do, remember they spent $50 million, $5 billion on the [Obamacare] server, if you remember.”
pageContext.analysis: The Obamacare website did not cost $5 billion. The Department of Health and Human Services offered an estimate that topped $800 million. A study by Bloomberg News, with a more expansive definition of federal spending, came up with an estimate of $2.1 billion.
